From d38dfe57a0c37b788de01e602f37add344f8c5d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:24:37 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 6: dedupe Checks tab + relative-time meta
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

GitHub's `commits/{sha}/check-runs` endpoint lists every run on the
commit, so a re-run leaves both old and new entries in the response
and the sidebar duplicates the row. `dedupeChecksByName` collapses by
name keeping the freshest by `completedAt` (falling back to
`startedAt`) and sorts alphabetically for a stable order.

Each row also grows a right-aligned meta cell: relative time of the
most recent run, or "running…" in the warn colour for in-flight
checks. The clickable details arrow now fades in on hover instead of
showing constantly, matching the demo's chrome.

The deeper "missing checks" audit (statuses API for non-Actions
sources, paging past 100) is left for a follow-up.
